1
00:00:02,002 --> 00:00:04,004
[ CRACKLING ]

2
00:00:28,562 --> 00:00:31,132
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

3
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:35,603
-COMMERCIAL FIRE WITHIN CITY
LIMITS AT ARCHER HIGH SCHOOL.

4
00:00:35,636 --> 00:00:37,938
BE ADVISED, WE HAVE REPORTS
OF GUNSHOTS AT AT THE SCENE,

5
00:00:37,971 --> 00:00:39,140
POSSIBLY INSIDE THE BUILDING.

6
00:00:39,173 --> 00:00:43,244
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

7
00:00:49,717 --> 00:00:51,285
-...HIGH SCHOOL,
WITH FIRE SHOWING

8
00:00:51,319 --> 00:00:55,623
ON THE SECOND FLOOR INSIDE
AND THE ROOF OF THE BUILDING.

9
00:00:58,459 --> 00:01:02,663
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

10
00:01:02,696 --> 00:01:04,432
[ HORN HONKS ]

11
00:01:14,542 --> 00:01:16,977
[ SIREN CHIRPS ]

12
00:01:18,879 --> 00:01:22,183
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

13
00:01:25,453 --> 00:01:27,788
[ BRAKES SQUEAL ]

14
00:01:27,821 --> 00:01:30,891
-WE HAVE A FIRE.

15
00:01:30,924 --> 00:01:32,593
-GO, GO, GO!

16
00:01:32,626 --> 00:01:34,562
[ ALARM RINGING ]

17
00:01:34,595 --> 00:01:36,430
-OH, MY GOD.

18
00:01:36,464 --> 00:01:39,066
-CAN YOU GET UP?

19
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:40,601
-I CAN'T FEEL MY LEGS.

20
00:01:40,634 --> 00:01:42,170
-LINE TO THE MAIN DOOR.

21
00:01:42,203 --> 00:01:43,937
-HERE WE GO, MOVE IT, MOVE IT!

22
00:01:43,971 --> 00:01:45,273
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

23
00:01:45,306 --> 00:01:49,777
-I CAN'T BELIEVE
I NEVER SAW IT BEFORE.

24
00:01:49,810 --> 00:01:52,646
WHAT I DID WAS WRONG.

25
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,383
-TAKE THAT LINE OUT THAT WAY,
OVER THERE.

26
00:01:55,416 --> 00:01:58,085
-GARY, YOU HOLD LINE SOMEHOW.

27
00:01:58,118 --> 00:02:00,087
-THIS WHOLE PLACE
IS ABOUT TO BLOW.

28
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,322
[ EXPLOSION, GLASS SHATTERS ]

29
00:02:01,355 --> 00:02:03,657
-I DIDN'T THINK IT WOULD END
THIS WAY.

30
00:02:03,691 --> 00:02:06,927
WAIT.

31
00:02:07,928 --> 00:02:12,132
[ EXPLOSIONS ]

32
00:02:18,439 --> 00:02:20,374
-BE ADVISED,
WE HAVE AN EXPLOSION,

33
00:02:20,408 --> 00:02:24,144
POSSIBLE CHEMICAL FIRE,
SECOND FLOOR, "A" SIDE.

34
00:02:24,178 --> 00:02:26,046
UPGRADE TO SECOND ALARM.

35
00:02:26,079 --> 00:02:29,049
[ HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING ]

36
00:02:30,318 --> 00:02:32,320
-AFTER WHAT
YOU'VE JUST BEEN THROUGH,

37
00:02:32,353 --> 00:02:34,655
YOU'RE LUCKY TO BE ALIVE.

38
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:37,991
I'M NOT SO SURE YOU CAN SAY THE
SAME ABOUT YOUR FRIEND, THOUGH.

39
00:02:38,025 --> 00:02:40,594
-HUH?

40
00:02:40,628 --> 00:02:41,629
-I'M SORRY.

41
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:43,931
UH, IF YOU REMEMBER
ANYTHING MORE,

42
00:02:43,964 --> 00:02:45,866
JUST, UH,
HAVE YOUR FOSTER PARENTS

43
00:02:45,899 --> 00:02:47,735
GET AHOLD OF ME, OKAY?

44
00:02:55,809 --> 00:02:58,379
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

45
00:03:04,785 --> 00:03:06,420
-ACCORDING TO CHIEF IRWIN,

46
00:03:06,454 --> 00:03:10,157
IT WAS ONE OF THE WORST CHEMICAL
FIRES HE'S SEEN IN MANY YEARS.

47
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:12,159
THE WEATHER
WASN'T COOPERATING, EITHER,

48
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:16,029
FORCING THE FIREFIGHTERS TO WORK
IN SUBZERO TEMPERATURES.

49
00:03:16,063 --> 00:03:17,998
LUCY VANDER,
A SUBSTITUTE TEACHER,

50
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:21,702
WAS ALSO ONE OF THE VOLUNTEERS
HELPING PUT OUT THE BLAZE.

51
00:03:21,735 --> 00:03:25,906
-IT WAS HEARTBREAKING TO SEE
THE SCHOOL LIKE THIS, UH,

52
00:03:25,939 --> 00:03:28,376
BUT I MOSTLY THINK ABOUT
THE FAMILIES

53
00:03:28,409 --> 00:03:30,578
AND, UH, THEIR LOVED ONES
AT THIS TIME.

54
00:03:30,611 --> 00:03:34,748
-THE MYSTERIOUS FIRE HAS LEFT
ARCHER HIGH SCHOOL SHUT DOWN

55
00:03:34,782 --> 00:03:36,450
PENDING AN INVESTIGATION.

56
00:03:36,484 --> 00:03:39,320
-THAT TAMMAND GIRL'S SUICIDE
LAST YEAR, AND NOW THIS.

57
00:03:39,353 --> 00:03:41,855
I MEAN, YOU SEE THESE THINGS
HAPPENING AT OTHER SCHOOLS.

58
00:03:41,889 --> 00:03:43,424
YOU JUST --

59
00:03:43,457 --> 00:03:47,027
YOU JUST NEVER IMAGINE IT
HAPPENING AT YOUR OWN.

60
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:49,096
YEAH. YEAH.

61
00:03:49,129 --> 00:03:52,366
YEAH, WELL, WE'RE DOING THE BEST
WE CAN UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES.

62
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,502
-OH, IT'S RIGHT THERE?
-THANK YOU.

63
00:03:56,003 --> 00:03:57,805
-PRINCIPAL DONATO?

64
00:03:57,838 --> 00:03:59,873
-HOLD ON ONE SECOND.

65
00:03:59,907 --> 00:04:03,110
YOU SHOULDN'T BE HERE.
WE'LL BE ISSUING A STATEMENT
LATER.

66
00:04:03,143 --> 00:04:04,445
IT'S THE PRESS.

67
00:04:04,478 --> 00:04:06,680
-I'M FROM PHIL BENSON'S OFFICE.

68
00:04:09,417 --> 00:04:11,519
-TERESA,
I'M GONNA HAVE TO, UH --

69
00:04:11,552 --> 00:04:13,721
I'M GONNA HAVE TO CALL YOU
RIGHT BACK.

70
00:04:13,754 --> 00:04:15,188
[ PHONE BEEPS ]

71
00:04:15,222 --> 00:04:17,558
WELL, UH, WHERE'S --
WHERE'S PHIL?

72
00:04:17,591 --> 00:04:19,627
-HE'S TIED UP WITH THE MAYOR.

73
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:20,861
-WHO -- WHO ARE YOU?

74
00:04:20,894 --> 00:04:22,963
-I'M THE ASSOCIATE COUNSEL
UNDER MR. BENSON.

75
00:04:22,996 --> 00:04:24,264
-REALLY?
[ SCOFFS ]

76
00:04:24,298 --> 00:04:25,633
WHAT, ARE YOU FRESH OUT
OF LAW SCHOOL?

77
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:27,067
THIS IS A BIG DEAL,
YOU UNDERSTAND?

78
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,869
-PRINCIPAL...
-YES?

79
00:04:28,902 --> 00:04:30,571
-I AM HERE TO TAKE CARE OF THIS,

80
00:04:30,604 --> 00:04:33,073
AND I NEED YOU TO COOPERATE,
UNDERSTAND?

81
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:35,509
-I'M SORRY, I'M SORRY.

82
00:04:35,543 --> 00:04:36,810
I SHOULDN'T HAVE SAID THAT.

83
00:04:36,844 --> 00:04:38,379
UH, I'M A LITTLE OUT OF SORTS

84
00:04:38,412 --> 00:04:40,548
WITH EVERYTHING
THAT'S GOING ON HERE TODAY.

85
00:04:40,581 --> 00:04:43,817
UH, LET ME JUST GO GET
THE FILES.

86
00:04:43,851 --> 00:04:45,853
-GREAT, I'LL BE RIGHT HERE.

87
00:04:57,698 --> 00:04:59,967
-I DON'T EVEN WANT TO THINK
ABOUT THE SETTLEMENT.

88
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,404
WHEN THEY'RE DONE WITH US,
ARCHER'S BANK ACCOUNT

89
00:05:03,437 --> 00:05:06,006
IS GONNA MAKE US LOOK LIKE
WE'RE LOCATED IN THE PROJECTS.

90
00:05:06,039 --> 00:05:07,274
-WILL THE PARENTS SUE?

91
00:05:07,307 --> 00:05:08,676
-THE PARENTS
ARE OUT OF THE PICTURE.

92
00:05:08,709 --> 00:05:09,977
FOSTER CARE.

93
00:05:10,010 --> 00:05:12,613
BUT YOU BETTER BELIEVE
THAT ONCE THIS THING LEAKS,

94
00:05:12,646 --> 00:05:16,316
EVERY AMBULANCE-CHASING,
BLOOD-SUCKING ATTORNEY

95
00:05:16,350 --> 00:05:19,052
IN THE STATE
IS GONNA BE CALLING THIS KID.

96
00:05:19,086 --> 00:05:20,754
NO OFFENSE.

97
00:05:20,788 --> 00:05:24,124
-I'M HERE TO BUILD A CASE THAT
ALEX'S OWN POOR DECISION-MAKING

98
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:25,759
LED US TO THIS SITUATION.

99
00:05:25,793 --> 00:05:28,629
AS A RESULT, ANY PUBLICITY OR
THREATS OF LAWSUIT WILL GO AWAY.

100
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:29,797
IN HERE?

101
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:31,832
-YEAH, YEAH.

102
00:05:33,701 --> 00:05:35,869
-THANK YOU.

103
00:05:38,205 --> 00:05:40,073
-HELLO, ALEX.

104
00:05:40,107 --> 00:05:42,109
-IS MY PAPERWORK DONE YET?

105
00:05:42,142 --> 00:05:43,544
-NOT YET.

106
00:05:43,577 --> 00:05:46,880
-ALEX, THIS IS LAURA SEDGEWICK.

107
00:05:46,914 --> 00:05:48,582
SHE, UH --

108
00:05:48,616 --> 00:05:51,018
SHE WANTS TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT LAST NIGHT.

109
00:05:51,051 --> 00:05:53,086
-I ALREADY TALKED TO THE POLICE.

110
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:56,590
-I-I WORK FOR THE SCHOOL BOARD.

111
00:05:56,624 --> 00:05:58,726
IT, UH, WON'T BE A PROBLEM

112
00:05:58,759 --> 00:06:00,961
IF WE TALK HERE IN PRIVATE
FOR A LITTLE WHILE, WILL IT?

113
00:06:00,994 --> 00:06:03,431
-NO, I'LL CHECK WITH
THE DETECTIVE, BUT, UH --

114
00:06:03,464 --> 00:06:05,098
-THERE WON'T BE A PROBLEM?

115
00:06:05,132 --> 00:06:07,334
-NO, NO.

116
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,503
THE, UH, PHONE LINES ARE DOWN,

117
00:06:09,537 --> 00:06:14,508
SO IF YOU NEED ME,
I'M...ON CHANNEL 2.

118
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:19,413
I'LL JUST LEAVE YOU TWO ALONE,
THEN.

119
00:06:34,528 --> 00:06:37,130
-I ALREADY TOLD THE POLICE
EVERYTHING I KNOW.

120
00:06:37,164 --> 00:06:40,601
-I DOUBT THAT.

121
00:06:40,634 --> 00:06:44,237
-WHEN MY PAPERWORK COMES
THROUGH, I'M ALLOWED TO LEAVE.

122
00:06:48,576 --> 00:06:51,344
-I SEE YOU'RE IN FOSTER CARE.

123
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:55,182
THAT MEANS THAT EVERY ASPECT
OF YOUR TRANSFER

124
00:06:55,215 --> 00:06:57,485
HAS TO GO THROUGH
SOCIAL SERVICES,

125
00:06:57,518 --> 00:07:01,655
AND I'M SURE YOU'RE AWARE
OF HOW EFFICIENT THEY CAN BE.

126
00:07:04,925 --> 00:07:08,662
I NEED YOU TO TELL ME
EVERY SINGLE DETAIL,

127
00:07:08,696 --> 00:07:12,866
EVEN THE ONES YOU DIDN'T TELL
THE POLICE.

128
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:16,436
-I TOLD YOU,
I TOLD THE POLICE EVERYTHING.

129
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:18,706
-[ SCOFFS ]

130
00:07:22,976 --> 00:07:26,914
-HOW DO I EVEN KNOW
YOU'RE NOT A COP?

131
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:31,919
-HERE'S MY CARD.

132
00:07:35,122 --> 00:07:38,258
OTHER THAN THAT, YOU'RE JUST
GONNA HAVE TO TRUST ME.

133
00:07:39,326 --> 00:07:42,062
I'M GONNA BE BLUNT.

134
00:07:42,095 --> 00:07:44,632
THE SOONER YOU'RE OUT OF THE
SCHOOL SYSTEM, THE BETTER.

135
00:07:44,665 --> 00:07:46,567
BUT BEFORE I CAN ALLOW THAT
TO HAPPEN,

136
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:49,870
I NEED TO KNOW EVERYTHING.

137
00:07:49,903 --> 00:07:53,006
EVERYTHING.

138
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:55,976
OFF THE RECORD.

139
00:07:56,009 --> 00:07:58,345
-[ CLEARS THROAT ]

140
00:07:58,378 --> 00:08:00,714
AND WHAT IF I DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO SAY?

141
00:08:00,748 --> 00:08:04,451
-WELL, THAT'S YOUR PREROGATIVE,
BUT I WILL WARN YOU

142
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:08,288
THAT IT COULD MAKE THE REST
OF YOUR FORMATIVE YEARS
EXTREMELY DIFFICULT.

143
00:08:19,232 --> 00:08:24,672
-W-WHAT EXACTLY...DO YOU WANT?

144
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:29,943
-WE CAN START
FROM THE BEGINNING.

145
00:08:34,748 --> 00:08:37,785
-IT ALL STARTED A FEW WEEKS AGO.

146
00:08:37,818 --> 00:08:40,087
LOOKING AROUND
THAT DETENTION ROOM,

147
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:43,456
IT WAS AS UNLIKELY A GROUP
AS YOU'D EVER FIND.

148
00:08:43,490 --> 00:08:47,961
A CLASS PRESIDENT,
HIS POPULAR GIRLFRIEND,

149
00:08:47,995 --> 00:08:51,398
TWO OF THE BIGGEST TROUBLEMAKERS
IN THE SCHOOL...

150
00:08:51,431 --> 00:08:54,434
AND ME.

151
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:56,970
-THIS IS ALL YOUR FAULT.

152
00:08:57,004 --> 00:08:59,773
-NO TALKING.

153
00:08:59,807 --> 00:09:01,441
-THEN IT'S GONNA BE HARD
FOR HER.

154
00:09:01,474 --> 00:09:04,377
-I SAID, NO TALKING!

155
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,786
-VERY NICE, GUYS.

156
00:09:12,820 --> 00:09:15,989
JUST GREAT.

157
00:09:16,023 --> 00:09:17,357
REALLY.

158
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:20,794
NO DEFENSE,
NO PLEAS OF INNOCENCE?

159
00:09:20,828 --> 00:09:23,764
IS SOMEONE GONNA AT LEAST TRY?

160
00:09:25,265 --> 00:09:26,967
YES, CAMERON.

161
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,971
-I HAVE NO IDEA WHAT THIS
IS ABOUT, MR. CONNOR.

162
00:09:31,004 --> 00:09:33,373
-"A" FOR EFFORT, CAMERON.

163
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:36,476
YOU SEE, THE ANSWER KEY TO THE
MIDTERM WAS STOLEN LAST WEEK.

164
00:09:36,509 --> 00:09:38,712
NOW, WHEN THIS WAS BROUGHT
TO MY ATTENTION,

165
00:09:38,746 --> 00:09:40,648
MY FIRST THOUGHT WAS, GREAT,

166
00:09:40,681 --> 00:09:44,151
NOW I HAVE TO WRITE
A NEW 250-QUESTION TEST.

167
00:09:44,184 --> 00:09:47,087
BUT THEN I REALIZED THAT
IF I KEPT THE SAME EXAM,

168
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:50,758
I COULD NAIL WHOEVER STOLE IT
AND EITHER PASSED IT OUT,

169
00:09:50,791 --> 00:09:54,962
OR, MORE LIKELY,
SOLD IT TO HIS BUDDIES.

170
00:09:55,996 --> 00:09:58,899
IF YOU ARE GOING TO CHEAT
ON A MULTIPLE-CHOICE TEST,

171
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:01,101
AT LEAST GET A COUPLE WRONG,
YOU KNOW?

172
00:10:01,134 --> 00:10:05,639
AIM FOR A B-PLUS TOPS,
ESPECIALLY YOU TWO CLOWNS.

173
00:10:05,673 --> 00:10:08,508
-[ Russian accent ] HOW
DO YOU KNOW WE DID NOT
JUST STUDY EXTRA HARD?

174
00:10:08,541 --> 00:10:09,910
-SAVE IT, PUTIN!

175
00:10:09,943 --> 00:10:12,179
NOW YOU'RE ALL GETTING ZEROS
ON THE MIDTERM.

176
00:10:12,212 --> 00:10:14,447
-WAIT, YOU CAN'T DO THAT!
THAT'S GONNA RUIN MY GPA!

177
00:10:14,481 --> 00:10:16,449
-I'VE NEVER DONE ANYTHING
LIKE THIS BEFORE.

178
00:10:16,483 --> 00:10:18,819
-YOU CHEATED!

179
00:10:18,852 --> 00:10:22,823
YOU ALL JUST CHEATED ON ONE OF
THE BIGGEST TESTS OF THE YEAR.

180
00:10:22,856 --> 00:10:25,693
YOU'RE LUCKY I DON'T BRING THIS
TO THE PRINCIPAL.

181
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:29,830
I NEED TO SPEAK TO YOU
OUTSIDE FOR A MINUTE.

182
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:38,772
-[ LAUGHING ]

183
00:10:38,806 --> 00:10:43,443
-WELL, WIN SOME, YOU LOSE SOME,
RIGHT, GUYS?

184
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:46,046
-DO YOU REALIZE
HOW SCREWED WE ARE?

185
00:10:46,079 --> 00:10:47,848
-NO, I DON'T.

186
00:10:47,881 --> 00:10:50,984
DO YOU FEEL SCREWED, RICKY?
-NYET.

187
00:10:51,018 --> 00:10:53,486
-IT'S EASY NOT TO CARE WHEN YOU
DON'T PLAN ON GOING TO COLLEGE.

188
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:55,288
-TELL YOUR BOYFRIEND
THAT ELITISM

189
00:10:55,322 --> 00:10:58,692
IS NO WAY TO GET ME TO HELP HIM
OUT OF THIS JAM.

190
00:10:58,726 --> 00:11:00,828
-YOU THINK WE CAN FIX THIS?

191
00:11:00,861 --> 00:11:02,329
-WE?

192
00:11:02,362 --> 00:11:04,664
WHO ARE YOU AGAIN?

193
00:11:04,698 --> 00:11:07,935
-ALEX.
-[ SCOFFS ]

194
00:11:07,968 --> 00:11:11,338
I DON'T NEED SOME LOSER MAKING
THINGS EVEN WORSE FOR ME.

195
00:11:11,371 --> 00:11:12,639
-[ LAUGHS ]

196
00:11:12,672 --> 00:11:16,243
-SO, DO YOU HAVE A PLAN?

197
00:11:16,276 --> 00:11:18,078
-AFTER A DAY IN I.S.S.,

198
00:11:18,111 --> 00:11:20,513
CAMERON AND RICKY
TOLD US THEIR PLAN.

199
00:11:20,547 --> 00:11:24,852
THEY'D BEEN THINKING ABOUT IT
SINCE THEIR FRESHMAN YEAR.

200
00:11:24,885 --> 00:11:27,087
IT WAS ACTUALLY A GOOD IDEA,

201
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:29,622
CONSIDERING THAT
THESE WERE THE GUYS

202
00:11:29,656 --> 00:11:34,027
THAT THOUGHT SETTING UP A STINK
BOMB WAS A REVOLUTIONARY ACT.

203
00:11:34,061 --> 00:11:37,697
THEIR PROBLEM WAS THAT THEY WERE
ALWAYS IN TROUBLE,

204
00:11:37,731 --> 00:11:39,767
SO THEY NEEDED STUDENTS
WITH ACCESS TO THINGS

205
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,368
THAT THEY COULDN'T GET TO.

206
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:45,806
I GUESS US GETTING CAUGHT ON
THAT TEST WAS THEIR LUCKY BREAK.

207
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:48,675
-IT'S THE PERFECT PLAN.

208
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,778
WHAT DO YOU THINK,
MR. PRESIDENT?

209
00:11:59,252 --> 00:12:01,221
-I THINK YOU'RE ALL IDIOTS.

210
00:12:01,254 --> 00:12:02,589
COME ON, CARLA.

211
00:12:03,656 --> 00:12:07,527
-THIS ISN'T FAIR, JACK.
-I'VE ALREADY GOTTEN
IN ENOUGH TROUBLE.

212
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,897
I'M NOT ABOUT TO GET IN ANY MORE
JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE
TELLING ME TO.

213
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:13,767
-WHY? WHATEVER, THEN YOU'LL
JUST FAIL CONNOR'S CLASS.

214
00:12:13,801 --> 00:12:16,736
HOW'S THAT GOING
TO LOOK TO DARTMOUTH?
-IT'S NOT GONNA LOOK PRETTY.

215
00:12:16,770 --> 00:12:20,307
-EXACTLY, SO WHY DON'T WE
DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT?

216
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:22,109
-I AM.
I'M GONNA STUDY.

217
00:12:22,142 --> 00:12:25,312
-IF YOU WERE ANY GOOD
AT STUDYING,

218
00:12:25,345 --> 00:12:28,515
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE BOUGHT THE
TEST ANSWERS IN THE FIRST PLACE.

219
00:12:29,449 --> 00:12:33,520
IF YOU REALLY CARED ABOUT ME,
YOU WOULD DO THIS!

220
00:12:33,553 --> 00:12:36,189
JACK, YOU OWE ME THIS!

221
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:42,262
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]
-JACK? JACK?!

222
00:12:42,295 --> 00:12:44,064
-WE'RE HERE, SON.

223
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:45,465
IT'S MOM AND DAD.

224
00:12:45,498 --> 00:12:48,235
YOU'RE IN A HOSPITAL.

225
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:49,769
-IT'S ALL MY FAULT.

226
00:12:49,803 --> 00:12:51,704
-SHUSH, BUDDY.
-IT'S ALL MY FAULT.

227
00:12:51,738 --> 00:12:54,407
IT'S ALL MY FAULT.
-WHAT'S HE SAYING?

228
00:12:54,441 --> 00:12:57,878
-IT'S ALL MY FAULT.

229
00:12:57,911 --> 00:12:59,947
-WHAT HAPPENED?
-HE JUST STARTED TALKING.

230
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:01,781
-HE'S GOING INTO
HYPOGLYCEMIC SHOCK.

231
00:13:01,815 --> 00:13:05,152
-STOP IT, JACK.
PLEASE, STOP IT.

232
00:13:05,185 --> 00:13:06,553
[ ALARM BLARING ]

233
00:13:06,586 --> 00:13:09,990
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

234
00:13:10,023 --> 00:13:12,792
-JACK!
[ CRYING ]

235
00:13:12,826 --> 00:13:14,828
HE'S OUR BOY.

236
00:13:14,862 --> 00:13:16,763
[ RAPID BEEPING ]

237
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:17,764
-YEAH.

238
00:13:17,797 --> 00:13:20,467
[ SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY ]

239
00:13:23,403 --> 00:13:25,438
-WE'RE GONNA GO TO THE PARTY
THIS WEEKEND.

240
00:13:25,472 --> 00:13:26,940
YOU GUYS DOWN FOR THAT?

241
00:13:26,974 --> 00:13:29,009
IT'S ON SATURDAY NIGHT.
IT'S AT PHIL'S HOUSE.

242
00:13:29,042 --> 00:13:30,777
SO WE JUST GOT
A LITTLE SHOPPING LIST

243
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:32,612
OF WHAT WE NEED
FOR THE HOMELESS SHELTER.

244
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:34,247
WE'RE GONNA DO PB&J's THIS WEEK.

245
00:13:34,281 --> 00:13:35,883
UM, AND AFTERWARDS,

246
00:13:35,916 --> 00:13:39,019
WE'RE GONNA GO TO THE TOP
OF THE WORLD AND GET CRUNK.

247
00:13:39,052 --> 00:13:40,921
IT'LL BE FUN.
YOU GUYS SHOULD COME.

248
00:13:40,954 --> 00:13:43,891
UMM --
IT SHOULD BE FUN --

249
00:13:43,924 --> 00:13:47,094
-JACK.
-WHAT?!

250
00:13:47,127 --> 00:13:49,396
-CAN I TALK TO YOU
ABOUT SOMETHING?

251
00:13:49,429 --> 00:13:51,764
-I'M BUSY.

252
00:13:51,798 --> 00:13:53,633
-IT'S ABOUT MR. CONNOR'S CLASS.

253
00:13:57,938 --> 00:13:59,406
-I'M GONNA GO DEAL WITH THIS.

254
00:13:59,439 --> 00:14:02,876
WE'LL TALK LATER, ALL RIGHT?

255
00:14:03,743 --> 00:14:05,112
THIS BETTER BE IMPORTANT.

256
00:14:08,515 --> 00:14:11,551
FAILING A CLASS IS BAD,
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT'S WORSE?

257
00:14:11,584 --> 00:14:13,686
GETTING EXPELLED.

258
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,923
-BUT IF IT WORKS,
WE COME OUT AHEAD.

259
00:14:15,956 --> 00:14:18,825
-WHAT DO YOU CARE, ANYWAYS?
YOU NEVER TALK IN CLASS.

260
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:21,328
YOU DON'T DO ANY SPORTS.
YOU DON'T DO ANY CLUBS.

261
00:14:21,361 --> 00:14:24,164
IS IT REALLY THAT BIG OF A DEAL
TO YOU IF YOU FAIL A CLASS?

262
00:14:24,197 --> 00:14:26,633
-I HAVE TO GET CERTAIN GRADES
TO STAY WHERE I AM.

263
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:29,202
-AND I'M SUPPOSED TO KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS?

264
00:14:29,236 --> 00:14:32,239
-I --
-COME ON, ALEX, WHAT?

265
00:14:32,272 --> 00:14:34,441
-I LIVE --

266
00:14:36,343 --> 00:14:39,412
I LIVE IN A FOSTER HOME.

267
00:14:39,446 --> 00:14:43,716
AND IN ORDER TO STAY WHERE I AM,
I HAVE TO DO WELL IN SCHOOL.

268
00:14:44,817 --> 00:14:46,386
THIS IS MY FIRST YEAR.

269
00:14:46,419 --> 00:14:49,422
I-I CAN'T FAIL A CLASS.

270
00:14:54,962 --> 00:14:57,264
-DO YOU LIKE YOUR FOSTER FAMILY?

271
00:14:59,766 --> 00:15:03,503
-COMPARED TO THE OTHERS...

272
00:15:03,536 --> 00:15:06,239
THIS ONE'S NOT SO BAD.

273
00:15:24,691 --> 00:15:26,159
LOOK, I'M NOT --

274
00:15:26,193 --> 00:15:30,163
I'M NOT SAYING DO IT BECAUSE
OF ME OR ANYONE ELSE.

275
00:15:30,197 --> 00:15:33,833
IF WE DON'T DO ANYTHING,
WE'RE ALL SCREWED.

276
00:15:35,235 --> 00:15:38,771
THERE'S A LOT MORE TO GAIN
THAN TO LOSE.

277
00:15:48,415 --> 00:15:51,418
-HOW DID YOU
EVENTUALLY BREAK JACK DOWN?

278
00:15:52,986 --> 00:15:55,888
-IS THAT WHAT IT SAYS,
THAT I BROKE HIM DOWN?

279
00:15:55,922 --> 00:15:57,424
-THAT'S WHAT IT SOUNDS LIKE.

280
00:15:57,457 --> 00:16:00,493
I MEAN, HE WAS THE LAST ONE
TO COME ALONG, RIGHT?

281
00:16:00,527 --> 00:16:02,829
-NO, JACK BROKE HIMSELF DOWN.

282
00:16:02,862 --> 00:16:04,164
-OH, REALLY?

283
00:16:04,197 --> 00:16:06,399
-HE DIDN'T WANT TO DO THIS.
-HMM.

284
00:16:06,433 --> 00:16:10,403
-NONE OF US WANTED TO DO THIS.
THERE WAS NO OTHER OPTION.

285
00:16:12,872 --> 00:16:14,474
WHAT ARE YOU WRITING?

286
00:16:18,945 --> 00:16:21,914
-KEEP GOING.

287
00:16:21,948 --> 00:16:24,184
-PULLING IT OFF.
WE WERE --

288
00:16:24,217 --> 00:16:27,087
WE WERE HELPING OURSELVES
WHILE HELPING EACH OTHER.

289
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:30,023
JACK WAS HELPING HIMSELF.

290
00:16:32,659 --> 00:16:36,629
WE JUST HAD TO MAKE SURE
THAT EVERYBODY DID THEIR PART.

291
00:16:36,663 --> 00:16:38,431
ARE YOU SURE IT'S BIG ENOUGH?

292
00:16:38,465 --> 00:16:40,800
-I DON'T KNOW!
IT WAS EXPENSIVE, OKAY?

293
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:45,838
DON'T SCREW THIS UP.
[ SIGHS ]

294
00:16:48,908 --> 00:16:51,211
-MR. GRIFFIN LEFT
SOME FILING FOR YOU,

295
00:16:51,244 --> 00:16:53,680
AND AFTER THAT, MRS. LYONS
NEEDS HER ATTENDANCE FINALIZED

296
00:16:53,713 --> 00:16:55,348
FOR PROGRESS REPORTS.

297
00:16:55,382 --> 00:16:56,416
-ANYTHING ELSE?

298
00:16:56,449 --> 00:16:59,452
-YOU SHOULD GET YOUR CHECK
ON FRIDAY.

299
00:16:59,486 --> 00:17:02,021
-GREAT.

300
00:17:02,055 --> 00:17:04,091
CAMERON AND RICKY WERE IN CHARGE

301
00:17:04,124 --> 00:17:06,126
OF GETTING
THE TEACHERS' PASSWORDS.

302
00:17:06,159 --> 00:17:09,329
RICKY HAD THIS CRAZY IDEA
OF GETTING A TRANSMITTER

303
00:17:09,362 --> 00:17:13,833
THAT WOULD GIVE US A RUNNING LOG
OF EVERYTHING TYPED INTO THE
SCHOOL COMPUTERS, BUT --

304
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:18,405
[ SNIFFLES ]
IT TURNED OUT THAT STUFF ONLY
EXISTED IN JAMES BOND MOVIES.

305
00:17:18,438 --> 00:17:22,142
CAMERON HAD
A MORE PRACTICAL APPROACH.

306
00:17:22,175 --> 00:17:25,612
HE KNEW HE COULD FIND
THE TEACHERS' LOG-INS
IN THE I.T. OFFICE,

307
00:17:25,645 --> 00:17:28,448
BUT HE WOULDN'T HAVE ENOUGH TIME
TO DO ANYTHING ELSE.

308
00:17:28,481 --> 00:17:30,217
HE STILL NEEDED A COPY
OF THE NETWORK

309
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:32,285
WHERE THE GRADES WERE STORED.
-[ CLEARS THROAT ]

310
00:17:32,319 --> 00:17:34,287
-THAT'S WHERE JACK AND I
CAME IN.

311
00:17:34,321 --> 00:17:35,422
-YES, JACK.

312
00:17:35,455 --> 00:17:37,957
-I WANT TO CALL
AN OFFICE MEETING.

313
00:17:39,526 --> 00:17:40,627
-WHAT?

314
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:42,262
-AS PRESIDENT
OF THE STUDENT COUNCIL,

315
00:17:42,295 --> 00:17:43,830
I WANT TO CALL
AN OFFICE MEETING.

316
00:17:43,863 --> 00:17:45,765
-ABOUT WHAT?

317
00:17:45,798 --> 00:17:49,068
-ABOUT A PROBLEM THAT OUR SCHOOL
HAS BEEN IGNORING SINCE
I'VE BEEN HERE.

318
00:17:54,006 --> 00:17:55,942
-ALL RIGHT.

319
00:17:55,975 --> 00:17:58,545
LET'S GET IT OVER WITH.

320
00:17:58,578 --> 00:18:02,215
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
IF I COULD HAVE YOUR
ATTENTION, PLEASE.

321
00:18:02,249 --> 00:18:05,718
OUR STUDENT COUNCIL PRESIDENT
HAS EXERCISED HIS RIGHT TO
CALL AN OFFICE MEETING.

322
00:18:05,752 --> 00:18:09,989
IF YOU COULD PLEASE JOIN US
IN THE STAFF LOUNGE, THANK YOU.

323
00:18:11,358 --> 00:18:14,227
-UM -- WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO?

324
00:18:14,261 --> 00:18:17,364
-HOLD DOWN THE FORT.

325
00:18:29,809 --> 00:18:31,944
[ PHONE DINGS ]

326
00:18:31,978 --> 00:18:34,381
[ PHONE VIBRATES ]

327
00:18:38,185 --> 00:18:40,086
-[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

328
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:57,837
-OH, GOD! JESUS! SHIT!

329
00:18:57,870 --> 00:19:00,973
SHIT! NO!

330
00:19:01,007 --> 00:19:02,242
-WHAT DID HE DO?

331
00:19:02,275 --> 00:19:04,477
WHERE IS HE GOING?
RICKY!

332
00:19:08,681 --> 00:19:10,016
-OH, NO!

333
00:19:10,049 --> 00:19:11,584
-WHAT HAPPENED?
WHAT DID YOU DO?

334
00:19:11,618 --> 00:19:13,653
-IT'S BURNT, IT'S BURNT,
IT'S BURNT!

335
00:19:13,686 --> 00:19:15,054
NO, YOU DON'T GOT TO SEE IT!

336
00:19:15,087 --> 00:19:17,023
IT'S A GODDAMN --
GOT A FIRE IN MY EYES!

337
00:19:17,056 --> 00:19:19,359
-LET ME SEE IT.
-NO!

338
00:19:19,392 --> 00:19:21,628
-HEY!
-OKAY, CAN I SEE IT?

339
00:19:21,661 --> 00:19:24,364
-DON'T USE
THAT KIND OF LANGUAGE.
-WE'RE TRYING TO HELP YOU.

340
00:19:24,397 --> 00:19:26,333
-YOU GONNA WANT ME
TO GO GET THE NURSE?

341
00:19:26,366 --> 00:19:29,068
-IF HE'S GONNA USE
THIS KIND OF...

342
00:19:36,743 --> 00:19:40,012
-OVER 150,000 STUDENTS
SKIP SCHOOL EVERY DAY

343
00:19:40,046 --> 00:19:41,348
BECAUSE THEY'RE BEING BULLIED,

344
00:19:41,381 --> 00:19:43,683
AND AT LEAST 1 IN EVERY 20
AMERICAN STUDENTS

345
00:19:43,716 --> 00:19:46,653
HAVE WITNESSED ANOTHER STUDENT
WITH A GUN AT THE SCHOOL.

346
00:19:46,686 --> 00:19:48,388
-WE KNOW THIS IS A PROBLEM,
JACK.

347
00:19:48,421 --> 00:19:51,491
WE GET TRAINED BY THE STATE
ON HOW TO DEAL WITH IT.

348
00:19:51,524 --> 00:19:53,092
[ RICKY SHOUTING IN DISTANCE ]

349
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:55,295
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

350
00:19:57,930 --> 00:19:59,366
-[ SIGHS ]

351
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:02,435
-SO, WHY ISN'T IT GETTING
ANY BETTER?

352
00:20:02,469 --> 00:20:06,673
-WELL, UH, TEENAGERS, BY NATURE,

353
00:20:06,706 --> 00:20:09,576
ARE NOT
THE MOST SYMPATHETIC GROUP.

354
00:20:09,609 --> 00:20:13,112
WE CAN'T JUST WAVE A MAGIC WAND
AND MAKE EVERYONE

355
00:20:13,145 --> 00:20:14,681
BE NICE TO EACH OTHER.
[ LAUGHTER ]

356
00:20:14,714 --> 00:20:16,616
-CALM DOWN. JUST LOWER
YOUR VOICE, ALL RIGHT?

357
00:20:16,649 --> 00:20:19,051
WE CAN FIGURE THIS OUT.
-NO, I'M NOT GONNA LOWER
MY VOICE, OKAY?!

358
00:20:19,085 --> 00:20:20,753
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

359
00:20:21,921 --> 00:20:24,424
-SHARED NETWORK DRIVE.

360
00:20:26,025 --> 00:20:29,128
-OKAY, SO WE'RE JUST GONNA KEEP
LETTING BAD THINGS HAPPEN?

361
00:20:29,161 --> 00:20:33,232
-WE STRIVE FOR EXCELLENCE HERE
AT ARCHER.

362
00:20:33,266 --> 00:20:35,735
ONE STUDENT AT A TIME.

363
00:20:35,768 --> 00:20:37,270
-I DON'T ACCEPT THAT.

364
00:20:37,304 --> 00:20:39,105
WHY NOT ONE SCHOOL AT A TIME?

365
00:20:39,138 --> 00:20:40,840
WE'RE A TEAM, AREN'T WE?

366
00:20:40,873 --> 00:20:42,409
WHY NOT ONE NATION AT A TIME?

367
00:20:42,442 --> 00:20:44,344
WHY DO WE HAVE TO STOP THERE?

368
00:20:44,377 --> 00:20:46,779
DO YOU REALIZE WHAT A STUDENT
GOES THROUGH?

369
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:56,823
[ RICKY SHOUTING IN DISTANCE ]

370
00:20:59,426 --> 00:21:01,594
-GO SEE THE NURSE!
-DON'T PUSH HIM, THOUGH.

371
00:21:01,628 --> 00:21:02,895
DON'T PUSH HIM.

372
00:21:02,929 --> 00:21:04,931
-...FIRE! SCREW YOU!

373
00:21:04,964 --> 00:21:07,334
-JUST GO TO THE NURSE!

374
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:12,372
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

375
00:21:12,405 --> 00:21:15,074
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING?

376
00:21:15,107 --> 00:21:17,310
-I-I --
-YOU HAVE GOT TO BE SHITTING ME.

377
00:21:17,344 --> 00:21:19,946
-THIS WAS HERE
BEFORE I GOT HERE.

378
00:21:19,979 --> 00:21:21,548
UH, IT WAS -- I --

379
00:21:21,581 --> 00:21:24,551
-JUST GET OUT OF HERE.
GO BACK TO CLASS.

380
00:21:24,584 --> 00:21:26,353
-YOU WANT ME TO --
-GO BACK TO CLASS.

381
00:21:26,386 --> 00:21:28,421
-ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

382
00:21:28,455 --> 00:21:29,989
-REALLY?

383
00:21:30,022 --> 00:21:32,359
-YOU THINK --
YOU THINK THAT WAS ME?
-AT LEAST CLOSE THE DOOR.

384
00:21:32,392 --> 00:21:34,394
OKAY, WHATEVER.

385
00:21:34,427 --> 00:21:36,295
-THERE YOU GO.
THEY'RE ALL UP THERE.

386
00:21:36,329 --> 00:21:38,398
-HE'S THERE.
-I KNOW, THERE'S
LIKE FOUR OF THEM.

387
00:21:38,431 --> 00:21:41,033
-HOW DO I GET TO
THE NEXT CHECKPOINT?

388
00:21:41,067 --> 00:21:43,069
-SO, HOW ARE YOU
GONNA MAKE IT UP TO US

389
00:21:43,102 --> 00:21:44,604
IF THESE NUMBERS DON'T WORK?

390
00:21:44,637 --> 00:21:45,972
-THEY'LL WORK.

391
00:21:46,005 --> 00:21:49,476
PLUS, I WOULDN'T WANT TO COME
BETWEEN YOU AND RICKY.

392
00:21:49,509 --> 00:21:52,545
-WE HAVE AN OPEN RELATIONSHIP.
[ MUNCHES ]

393
00:21:52,579 --> 00:21:54,481
-NICE JOB WITH THAT BULLSHIT

394
00:21:54,514 --> 00:21:57,517
YOU TOLD ME TO FEED DONATO,
BY THE WAY.

395
00:21:57,550 --> 00:21:59,419
HEY, YOU CRIMINAL MASTERMINDS

396
00:21:59,452 --> 00:22:01,287
FIGURE OUT HOW TO GET THE GRADES
BACK IN THE SYSTEM YET?

397
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:02,655
-YEAH, WE GOT IT.

398
00:22:02,689 --> 00:22:05,124
-AS LONG AS I CAN GET BACK IN
THE I.T. OFFICE.

399
00:22:07,093 --> 00:22:08,695
-EVEN THOUGH
IT WAS DEPARTMENT POLICY

400
00:22:08,728 --> 00:22:10,763
TO LET STUDENTS MAKE UP ANY LABS
THAT THEY MISSED,

401
00:22:10,797 --> 00:22:13,533
CAMERON CARING
ABOUT MISSING CLASS

402
00:22:13,566 --> 00:22:17,003
SHOULD HAVE GOTTEN
HIS ATTENTION,

403
00:22:17,036 --> 00:22:19,706
BUT FAUSTIN DIDN'T NOTICE.

404
00:22:22,375 --> 00:22:26,178
-[ CLEARS THROAT ]

405
00:22:26,212 --> 00:22:28,014
-MR. FAUSTIN?

406
00:22:28,047 --> 00:22:29,115
-YEAH.

407
00:22:29,148 --> 00:22:30,850
-I NEED TO GO TO THE RESTROOM.

408
00:22:33,453 --> 00:22:35,555
-AND I CARE ABOUT THAT WHY?

409
00:22:35,588 --> 00:22:40,359
-FAUSTIN DIDN'T NOTICE MUCH,
SO LONG AS IT DIDN'T REQUIRE
ANY EFFORT ON HIS PART.

410
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:24,303
[ BELL RINGING ]

411
00:23:40,687 --> 00:23:42,855
-I'M TELLING YOU...
[ WHISPERING ]

412
00:23:45,492 --> 00:23:47,193
WHAT'S UP, FREAK?!
[ TRAY THUDS ]

413
00:23:47,226 --> 00:23:49,361
[ LAUGHTER ]

414
00:23:49,395 --> 00:23:51,163
-WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

415
00:23:51,197 --> 00:23:53,466
-IT'S COOL, BRO.

416
00:23:55,001 --> 00:23:57,570
-ALEX.

417
00:23:57,604 --> 00:24:01,007
-AND OVERNIGHT,
EVERYTHING CHANGED.

418
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:04,310
[ TECHNO MUSIC PLAYS ]

419
00:24:10,116 --> 00:24:11,317
-OKAY?

420
00:24:11,350 --> 00:24:12,985
[ Laughing ]
AGAIN, ONE MORE TIME.

421
00:24:13,019 --> 00:24:16,055
-THEY EVEN INVITED ME
TO CELEBRATE OUR VICTORY.

422
00:24:16,088 --> 00:24:17,857
EVERYTHING WAS PERFECT.

423
00:24:17,890 --> 00:24:21,694
IT WAS LIKE WE NEVER EVEN GOT
CAUGHT IN THE FIRST PLACE.

424
00:24:21,728 --> 00:24:25,565
WE WERE ON TOP OF THE WORLD.

425
00:24:29,068 --> 00:24:31,403
THERE WAS NO WAY
ANY OF US COULD HAVE GUESSED

426
00:24:31,437 --> 00:24:34,040
WHAT WOULD HAPPEN NEXT.

427
00:24:37,810 --> 00:24:41,313
-GOOD NIGHT, MOM.
GOOD NIGHT, DAD.

428
00:25:15,882 --> 00:25:17,784
[ COMPUTER DINGS ]

429
00:25:24,691 --> 00:25:26,325
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

430
00:25:33,165 --> 00:25:35,935
[ PHONE VIBRATES ]
[ GASPS ]

431
00:25:52,518 --> 00:25:54,453
-YO, JUST LET ME HANDLE THIS,
ALL RIGHT?

432
00:25:54,486 --> 00:25:56,322
-OKAY, JUST LOOK FOR ME, OKAY?
-HOW?

433
00:25:56,355 --> 00:25:58,591
-I DIDN'T WANT ANY OF THEM.
-SHE --

434
00:25:58,625 --> 00:26:00,126
-WE DON'T EVEN UNDERSTAND
WHAT'S GOING ON.

435
00:26:00,159 --> 00:26:02,795
-I DON'T CARE, OKAY, BECAUSE
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

436
00:26:02,829 --> 00:26:05,564
-STOP!
-WHAT'S UP, GUYS?

437
00:26:09,636 --> 00:26:11,003
WHAT HAPPENED?

438
00:26:12,772 --> 00:26:16,776
-WE -- WAS ANYBODY BOTHERING YOU
LAST NIGHT, ALEX?

439
00:26:18,210 --> 00:26:20,579
LIKE, ONLINE?

440
00:26:20,613 --> 00:26:24,083
-I'M ONLY ALLOWED TO USE
THE INTERNET FOR SCHOOL WORK.

441
00:26:24,116 --> 00:26:26,252
-YOU'RE USELESS.

442
00:26:26,285 --> 00:26:27,620
-WHY?

443
00:26:27,654 --> 00:26:29,321
-WE ALL GOT MESSAGES LAST NIGHT.

444
00:26:29,355 --> 00:26:31,190
SOMEONE ONLINE
KNOWS WHAT WE DID.

445
00:26:31,223 --> 00:26:34,093
-WHO ARE THEY FROM?
-WHO CARES WHO THEY WERE FROM?

446
00:26:34,126 --> 00:26:36,328
IF SHE HADN'T KILLED HERSELF, NO
ONE WOULD EVEN KNOW WHO SHE WAS.

447
00:26:36,362 --> 00:26:38,765
-HEY, HEY, YOUR BOYFRIEND
WOULD KNOW WHO SHE WAS, OKAY?

448
00:26:38,798 --> 00:26:40,366
-WE ALL KNEW WHO SHE WAS.
I KNEW WHO SHE WAS.

449
00:26:40,399 --> 00:26:42,201
RICKY KNEW WHO SHE WAS, AND JACK
DEFINITELY KNEW WHO SHE IS.

450
00:26:42,234 --> 00:26:45,805
-IT DOESN'T MATTER.
-WHO ARE YOU EVEN TALKING ABOUT?

451
00:26:45,838 --> 00:26:47,606
-BRITTANY.

452
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:50,843
BRITTANY TAMMAND
SENT US THE MESSAGES.

453
00:27:02,154 --> 00:27:04,356
-WHO'S BRITTANY?

454
00:27:04,390 --> 00:27:06,425
ALEX.

455
00:27:08,327 --> 00:27:12,264
ALEX, WHO IS BRITTANY?

456
00:27:12,298 --> 00:27:14,466
I KNOW YOU'RE TIRED,

457
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:16,402
BUT I NEED YOU
TO KEEP GOING, OKAY?

458
00:27:16,435 --> 00:27:17,737
WHO WAS BRITTANY?

459
00:27:17,770 --> 00:27:19,706
-SHE WAS A TYPICAL PUNCHING BAG.

460
00:27:19,739 --> 00:27:22,742
-SHE GOT IN A LOT OF FIGHTS
OR...?

461
00:27:22,775 --> 00:27:24,410
-YOU WORK FOR THE SCHOOL BOARD,

462
00:27:24,443 --> 00:27:27,413
BUT YOU HAVE NO IDEA WHAT
ACTUALLY HAPPENS IN SCHOOL.

463
00:27:27,446 --> 00:27:29,816
-SLIGHTLY MORE COMPLICATED
THAN THAT.

464
00:27:29,849 --> 00:27:32,084
-IT DOESN'T SEEM
THAT COMPLICATED.

465
00:27:32,118 --> 00:27:34,754
KID'S POPULAR, COMES FROM
A GOOD FAMILY,

466
00:27:34,787 --> 00:27:37,656
GETS GOOD GRADES,
PLAYS SPORTS, WHATEVER.

467
00:27:37,690 --> 00:27:40,292
THEY CAN DO WHATEVER THEY WANT.

468
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:44,330
YOU KNOW, IN AN IDEAL SYSTEM,
THE KIDS WOULD RUN THE SCHOOL.

469
00:27:44,363 --> 00:27:48,634
THEY'D MAKE THE RULES
AND DISH OUT THE PUNISHMENTS.

470
00:27:48,667 --> 00:27:51,670
ADULTS HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT KIDS ARE REALLY LIKE.

471
00:27:51,704 --> 00:27:55,241
THE OLDER YOU ARE,
THE MORE YOU FORGET.

472
00:27:55,274 --> 00:27:58,210
-I TAKE IT YOU HAVEN'T READ
"LORD OF THE FLIES" YET, HUH?

473
00:27:58,244 --> 00:28:00,179
NEVER MIND.

474
00:28:00,212 --> 00:28:01,981
KEEP GOING.

475
00:28:02,014 --> 00:28:04,050
-THEY SAY SHE HAD
A TERRIBLE REPUTATION.

476
00:28:04,083 --> 00:28:07,519
-SHE SLEPT AROUND,
SHE WAS PROMISCUOUS?

477
00:28:07,553 --> 00:28:09,488
-MAYBE, MAYBE NOT.

478
00:28:09,521 --> 00:28:11,157
SINCE WHEN DO KIDS CARE

479
00:28:11,190 --> 00:28:13,059
IF THE RUMORS THAT THEY HEAR
IN THE HALLS ARE TRUE?

480
00:28:13,092 --> 00:28:16,095
-I DON'T KNOW. YOU TELL ME.
WHAT HAPPENED TO HER?

481
00:28:17,496 --> 00:28:20,800
-IT WAS A YEAR BEFORE I CAME
TO ARCHER, BUT APPARENTLY,
SHE DROWNED HERSELF.

482
00:28:23,803 --> 00:28:26,138
SHE LEFT A NOTE ON THE SHORE.

483
00:28:27,606 --> 00:28:30,042
NO ONE EVEN NOTICED.

484
00:28:30,076 --> 00:28:31,911
SHE JUST WENT IN,
AND THEN SHE WAS GONE.

485
00:28:31,944 --> 00:28:35,114
-W-WHAT ARE YOU SAYING, ALEX,
THAT -- THAT BRITTANY TAMMAND

486
00:28:35,147 --> 00:28:38,885
WAS TRYING TO REACH YOU GUYS
FROM BEYOND THE GRAVE?

487
00:28:38,918 --> 00:28:41,320
-NO, I'M TELLING YOU
THAT WHOEVER KNEW WHAT WE DID

488
00:28:41,353 --> 00:28:44,156
MADE AN ONLINE PROFILE
AS BRITTANY TAMMAND

489
00:28:44,190 --> 00:28:46,258
TO GET OUR ATTENTION.

490
00:28:47,726 --> 00:28:49,428
AND IT WORKED.

491
00:28:49,461 --> 00:28:50,629
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

492
00:28:50,662 --> 00:28:52,799
-MR. AND MRS. STANTON?
-YES.

493
00:28:52,832 --> 00:28:55,367
-DETECTIVE HUTISAWA
OF COUNTY HOMICIDE.

494
00:28:55,401 --> 00:28:58,704
I HEAR YOUR SON'S BEEN SAYING
SOME PRETTY DISCONCERTING
THINGS.

495
00:28:58,737 --> 00:29:00,940
-[ SIGHS ]
-JACK'S A GOOD BOY.

496
00:29:00,973 --> 00:29:03,042
HE WOULD NEVER HURT ANYONE.

497
00:29:03,075 --> 00:29:05,444
-WELL, SOMETIMES
AFTER TRAUMATIC EVENTS,

498
00:29:05,477 --> 00:29:08,014
PEOPLE LET THE GUILT OF NOT
BEING ABLE TO STOP WHAT HAPPENED

499
00:29:08,047 --> 00:29:10,216
TRICK THEM INTO THINKING
THEY'RE THE ONES TO BLAME.

500
00:29:10,249 --> 00:29:12,651
-YOU THINK THAT'S
WHAT'S HAPPENING NOW?

501
00:29:12,684 --> 00:29:15,988
-NO, NOT REALLY, BUT I DO
THINK THAT JACK COULD
TELL ME SOMETHING

502
00:29:16,022 --> 00:29:19,325
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED
THAT I DON'T KNOW YET.

503
00:29:40,779 --> 00:29:42,982
-IS MY PAPERWORK DONE YET?

504
00:29:43,015 --> 00:29:45,852
-MISS SEDGEWICK,
MAY I HAVE A WORD, PLEASE?

505
00:29:46,685 --> 00:29:50,056
-[ SIGHS ]
-[ SIGHS ]

506
00:29:58,197 --> 00:29:59,465
WHAT?

507
00:29:59,498 --> 00:30:02,034
-I JUST GOT A CALL
FROM THE HOSPITAL.
-AND?

508
00:30:02,068 --> 00:30:04,370
-JACK STANTON,
THE STUDENT IN THE I.C.U.,

509
00:30:04,403 --> 00:30:07,673
HE'S ON THE VERGE OF AN
ANESTHESIA-INDUCED CONFESSION.

510
00:30:07,706 --> 00:30:09,575
-WHAT'S HE GUILTY OF?
-THEY'RE NOT SURE,

511
00:30:09,608 --> 00:30:12,011
BUT IT MEANS THERE'S SOMETHING
ELSE TO THE STORY WE
DON'T KNOW ABOUT.

512
00:30:12,044 --> 00:30:15,114
-WHATEVER IT IS, IF HE CONFESSES
ANYTHING ON A MORPHINE DRIP,
IT'LL NEVER HOLD UP IN COURT.

513
00:30:15,147 --> 00:30:17,416
-I KNOW, I KNOW.
THE DETECTIVE SAID THAT, TOO.

514
00:30:17,449 --> 00:30:23,155
BUT...IF WE CAN GET ALEX
TO IMPLICATE JACK...

515
00:30:24,123 --> 00:30:26,625
...THE SCHOOL
COULD ESCAPE LIABILITY.

516
00:30:28,094 --> 00:30:30,162
-[ SIGHS ]

517
00:30:30,196 --> 00:30:32,731
IN THE MEANTIME,
GET ME WHATEVER YOU HAVE

518
00:30:32,764 --> 00:30:34,700
ON BRITTANY TAMMAND.
[ DOOR OPENS ]

519
00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:42,108
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

520
00:30:43,642 --> 00:30:45,978
-EVERYTHING OKAY?

521
00:30:49,882 --> 00:30:53,219
-I WANT YOU TO TELL ME MORE
ABOUT JACK.

522
00:30:53,252 --> 00:30:55,254
-I AM TELLING YOU ABOUT JACK.

523
00:30:55,287 --> 00:30:57,389
I'M -- I'M TELLING YOU
ABOUT EVERYONE.

524
00:30:57,423 --> 00:31:00,259
-YEAH, BUT WHAT WAS HE LIKE
BEFORE YOU GOT INVOLVED
IN ALL OF THIS?

525
00:31:01,994 --> 00:31:05,965
-HE WAS POPULAR.
HE WAS...CLASS PRESIDENT.

526
00:31:05,998 --> 00:31:08,267
HE WAS IN A -- A BUNCH OF CLUBS.
HE --

527
00:31:08,300 --> 00:31:12,004
GIRLS LIKED HIM.
HE SEEMED LIKE A GOOD GUY.

528
00:31:12,038 --> 00:31:14,606
-HE BOUGHT TEST ANSWERS

529
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:19,711
AND THEN LIED AND CHEATED
HIS WAY OUT OF IT WHEN
HE GOT CAUGHT.

530
00:31:20,913 --> 00:31:22,848
-I DID THAT, TOO.

531
00:31:22,881 --> 00:31:25,184
-YEAH, BUT YOU DID THAT
SO YOU WOULDN'T GET KICKED
OUT OF YOUR FOSTER HOME.

532
00:31:25,217 --> 00:31:27,019
YOU'RE A VICTIM OF THE SYSTEM.

533
00:31:27,053 --> 00:31:28,354
JACK WAS ON TOP OF THE SYSTEM.

534
00:31:28,387 --> 00:31:30,389
-NO, HE WANTED
TO GO TO DARTMOUTH.

535
00:31:30,422 --> 00:31:31,723
-[ CHUCKLES ]

536
00:31:31,757 --> 00:31:34,360
DON'T -- DON'T YOU THINK
THAT'S A LITTLE EXTREME?

537
00:31:34,393 --> 00:31:37,329
A LITTLE SELFISH
AND -- AND CONNIVING?

538
00:31:38,564 --> 00:31:40,532
-I-I DON'T KNOW.
HE'S MY FRIEND.

539
00:31:40,566 --> 00:31:44,236
-WOULDN'T A REAL FRIEND HAVE
TRIED TO TALK YOU OUT OF
GETTING INTO THIS MESS?

540
00:31:44,270 --> 00:31:48,340
THEY USED YOU TO GET
INTO THE PRINCIPAL'S OFFICE
BECAUSE YOU WERE THE NOBODY.

541
00:31:48,374 --> 00:31:50,842
DON'T YOU THINK THEY
TOOK ADVANTAGE OF THAT?

542
00:31:50,876 --> 00:31:52,911
-NO, WE WERE A TEAM.
-WHAT KIND OF TEAM MEMBER

543
00:31:52,945 --> 00:31:56,248
LETS HIS FRIENDS DIE
SO HE CAN GO TO COLLEGE?!

544
00:31:56,282 --> 00:32:00,419
JACK DIDN'T CARE ABOUT YOU!
YOU WERE A NOBODY TO JACK!

545
00:32:00,452 --> 00:32:02,989
YOU WERE NOT JACK'S FRIEND!

546
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:11,497
LOOK, ALEX.

547
00:32:11,530 --> 00:32:14,600
ALEX, LOOK.
-[ CRIES ]

548
00:32:14,633 --> 00:32:16,168
-I'M -- I'M NOT -- I'M --

549
00:32:16,202 --> 00:32:17,936
[ SIGHS ]

550
00:32:17,970 --> 00:32:20,772
I'M -- I'M NOT TRYING
TO UPSET YOU.

551
00:32:20,806 --> 00:32:23,009
I JUST REALLY WANT YOU
TO THINK ABOUT

552
00:32:23,042 --> 00:32:26,078
WHAT KIND OF PERSON
WOULD DO THIS

553
00:32:26,112 --> 00:32:28,614
IF THEY DIDN'T
ABSOLUTELY HAVE TO.

554
00:32:29,515 --> 00:32:33,119
MAYBE JACK WASN'T THE PERSON
THAT YOU THOUGHT HE WAS.

555
00:32:35,554 --> 00:32:38,290
JACK WAS NOT A GOOD GUY.

556
00:32:40,292 --> 00:32:41,460
-NO.

557
00:32:41,493 --> 00:32:43,962
NO, I KNOW HIM.

558
00:32:43,996 --> 00:32:45,497
[ SNIFFLES ]

559
00:32:45,531 --> 00:32:47,399
HE MAY HAVE NOT MADE
THE RIGHT DECISIONS,

560
00:32:47,433 --> 00:32:53,039
BUT...AT THE END OF THE DAY,
HE WAS A GOOD PERSON.

561
00:32:53,972 --> 00:32:57,143
I PROMISE, HE WAS GOOD.

562
00:33:03,315 --> 00:33:04,816
[ SNIFFLES ]

563
00:33:06,818 --> 00:33:11,190
-SO, UM, WHAT DID --

564
00:33:11,223 --> 00:33:15,061
WHAT DID YOU DO WHEN THE OTHERS
TOLD YOU ABOUT THE MESSAGES?

565
00:33:17,029 --> 00:33:19,498
-[ SNIFFLES ]
EVERYONE WAS JUST FREAKED OUT.

566
00:33:19,531 --> 00:33:20,766
-YEAH.

567
00:33:20,799 --> 00:33:23,469
-[ SNIFFLES ]

568
00:33:23,502 --> 00:33:28,240
I JUST -- I JUST TRIED TO
PRETEND IT WASN'T HAPPENING.

569
00:33:29,075 --> 00:33:31,043
CAMERON AND RICKY
WERE NOTORIOUS,

570
00:33:31,077 --> 00:33:34,046
AND CARLA AND JACK
WERE THE MOST POPULAR.

571
00:33:34,080 --> 00:33:37,416
IT COULD HAVE BEEN ANYONE
MESSING WITH THEM.

572
00:33:37,449 --> 00:33:40,352
I JUST FIGURED AS LONG AS NO ONE
WAS CONTACTING ME,

573
00:33:40,386 --> 00:33:43,322
THEN IT WAS JUST SOMEONE
PLAYING A TRICK.

574
00:33:45,191 --> 00:33:48,260
BUT I WAS REALLY WRONG.

575
00:33:59,471 --> 00:34:01,907
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

576
00:34:05,577 --> 00:34:07,446
THEY HAVE MY BIRTHDAY,

577
00:34:07,479 --> 00:34:10,516
MY ADDRESS, MY --
MY PHONE NUMBER, EVERYTHING.

578
00:34:10,549 --> 00:34:12,984
HOW DID THEY GET THIS STUFF?
I DIDN'T SET UP THIS ACCOUNT.

579
00:34:13,018 --> 00:34:15,454
-WELL, WHOEVER
IT IS, THEY GO TO ARCHER.
I MEAN, LOOK AT THE PICTURE.

580
00:34:15,487 --> 00:34:18,990
-I SAY WE FIND OUT WHO THEY ARE,
WE BEAT THEM DOWN, AND THEY
NEVER TRY THIS GAME AGAIN!

581
00:34:19,024 --> 00:34:21,560
-LOOK HOW SCARED THIS PERSON HAS
US WITHOUT EVEN DOING ANYTHING?

582
00:34:21,593 --> 00:34:25,231
ALL RIGHT, IF THEY DON'T WANT US
TO FIND OUT WHO THEY ARE,
THEN WE WON'T.

583
00:34:25,264 --> 00:34:28,567
-WHAT DO YOU THINK SHE WANTS
FROM US?

584
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:29,801
-I DON'T KNOW.

585
00:34:29,835 --> 00:34:31,670
[ COMPUTER DINGS ]

586
00:34:31,703 --> 00:34:33,405
-YOU'RE ABOUT TO FIND OUT.

587
00:34:34,773 --> 00:34:36,875
-OPEN IT.

588
00:34:37,743 --> 00:34:39,211
OPEN IT.

589
00:34:41,147 --> 00:34:43,649
-[ Digitized voice ]
YOU'RE EARLY...

590
00:34:43,682 --> 00:34:46,452
AND NOT ALONE.

591
00:34:49,655 --> 00:34:51,923
-WHO ARE YOU?

592
00:34:51,957 --> 00:34:54,193
-I'M BRITTANY TAMMAND, DUH.

593
00:34:54,226 --> 00:34:56,928
-NO, YOU'RE NOT.
BRITTANY TAMMAND'S DEAD.

594
00:34:56,962 --> 00:34:58,997
-YOU ALL KNEW ME
WHEN I WAS ALIVE.

595
00:34:59,030 --> 00:35:00,699
-NO, I NEVER KNEW YOU.

596
00:35:00,732 --> 00:35:03,435
-BUT YOUR FRIENDS DID.

597
00:35:03,469 --> 00:35:07,439
AND THAT MAKES YOU GUILTY
BY ASSOCIATION.

598
00:35:07,473 --> 00:35:09,741
CHEATER.

599
00:35:09,775 --> 00:35:11,743
-WHAT DO YOU WANT?

600
00:35:11,777 --> 00:35:13,812
-I WANT WHAT'S RIGHTFULLY MINE,

601
00:35:13,845 --> 00:35:16,148
AND YOU AND YOUR FRIENDS
ARE GOING TO HELP ME GET IT.

602
00:35:16,182 --> 00:35:18,550
-RIGHTFULLY YOURS?
WHAT DOES THAT EVEN MEAN?

603
00:35:18,584 --> 00:35:21,820
-I'LL BE GIVING EACH
OF YOU LITTLE CHORES
IN THE UPCOMING DAYS.

604
00:35:21,853 --> 00:35:25,724
IF ONE OF YOU FAILS,
THEN I'LL EXPOSE THEM
TO THE ADMINISTRATION.

605
00:35:25,757 --> 00:35:28,227
BUT FOR YOUR SAKES,
I HOPE YOU SUCCEED,

606
00:35:28,260 --> 00:35:32,164
BECAUSE SOMETHING
TELLS ME LOYALTY IS YOUR
LITTLE GROUP'S STRONG SUIT.

607
00:35:32,198 --> 00:35:33,765
-YOU'RE FULL OF SHIT.
-OH, AM I?

608
00:35:33,799 --> 00:35:35,567
-CALLING US CHEATERS
DOESN'T PROVE ANYTHING.

609
00:35:35,601 --> 00:35:38,204
WE'VE DONE NOTHING WRONG.
YOU'RE A LIAR.

610
00:35:38,237 --> 00:35:40,138
[ COMPUTER DINGS ]

611
00:35:42,774 --> 00:35:44,976
-OPEN IT!

612
00:35:45,977 --> 00:35:48,314
[ COMPUTER DINGS ]

613
00:35:48,347 --> 00:35:52,418
-I HAVE MORE,
BUT THIS SHOULD BE ENOUGH TO
GET THE PRINCIPAL'S ATTENTION.

614
00:35:54,620 --> 00:35:56,288
-I'LL KILL YOU.

615
00:35:56,322 --> 00:36:00,025
-[ LAUGHS ]
I'M ALREADY DEAD, REMEMBER?

616
00:36:00,058 --> 00:36:02,794
-LOOK, WHAT DO YOU WANT US
TO DO?

617
00:36:02,828 --> 00:36:04,996
-YOU'LL FIND OUT SOON ENOUGH.

618
00:36:05,030 --> 00:36:07,266
I HAVE ALL YOUR PHONE NUMBERS.

619
00:36:07,299 --> 00:36:09,568
BE ON THE LOOKOUT.

620
00:36:09,601 --> 00:36:11,102
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

621
00:36:15,106 --> 00:36:16,508
-WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

622
00:36:16,542 --> 00:36:18,644
-WE'RE GONNA FIND OUT
WHOEVER THIS IS.

623
00:36:18,677 --> 00:36:22,381
UNTIL THEN, WE DO EXACTLY
WHAT SHE SAYS, OKAY?

624
00:36:22,414 --> 00:36:24,716
-JACK TRIED TO BE BRAVE
AND TAKE CHARGE,

625
00:36:24,750 --> 00:36:30,088
BUT I KNEW HE AND EVERYONE ELSE
WERE JUST AS AFRAID AS I WAS.

626
00:36:30,121 --> 00:36:33,124
[ PHONE VIBRATES ]

627
00:36:35,561 --> 00:36:38,997
I MEAN, WE HAD NO IDEA WHAT
BRITTANY WAS GONNA ASK US TO DO

628
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:43,134
OR -- OR HOW TO TRACK DOWN
WHO SHE WAS.

629
00:36:43,168 --> 00:36:45,871
-WHY DO YOU THINK THAT CAMERON
WAS THE FIRST ONE

630
00:36:45,904 --> 00:36:47,673
THAT BRITTANY CONTACTED?

631
00:36:47,706 --> 00:36:50,609
-WELL, EVERYONE AT ARCHER KNOWS
THAT CAMERON'S THE GUY TO GO TO

632
00:36:50,642 --> 00:36:53,078
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING
THAT'S HARD TO FIND.

633
00:36:53,111 --> 00:36:54,179
-LIKE DRUGS?

634
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:55,847
-I SAID HARD TO FIND,

635
00:36:55,881 --> 00:37:00,218
LIKE STOLEN ANSWER KEYS
AND TEACHER LOG-INS.

636
00:37:00,252 --> 00:37:02,588
ONE OF THE WAYS THAT CAMERON
USED TO MAKE MONEY

637
00:37:02,621 --> 00:37:05,156
WAS BY MAKING
HIGH-QUALITY FAKE I.D.s.

638
00:37:05,190 --> 00:37:06,592
LIKE, THE REALLY GOOD ONES,

639
00:37:06,625 --> 00:37:10,562
THE TYPE THAT SCAN
AT A LIQUOR STORE.

640
00:37:10,596 --> 00:37:13,265
SO, BRITTANY TEXTED CAMERON
ALL THE INFORMATION SHE WANTED,

641
00:37:13,299 --> 00:37:15,501
AND -- AND FOR HIM, IT WAS EASY.

642
00:37:15,534 --> 00:37:17,636
HE'D DONE IT A MILLION TIMES.

643
00:37:17,669 --> 00:37:21,340
-DON'T LOOK LIKE NO BRITTANY
I REMEMBER.

644
00:37:32,751 --> 00:37:35,186
-DO YOU THINK SHE'LL LEAVE US
ALONE NOW?

645
00:37:36,555 --> 00:37:38,957
-NO ONE GOES THROUGH
THIS MUCH TROUBLE TO BUY BEER.

646
00:37:38,990 --> 00:37:41,793
-HEY, WHY DOES THIS
HAVE MY ADDRESS?

647
00:37:41,827 --> 00:37:43,862
-THAT'S WHAT SHE ASKED FOR.

648
00:37:43,895 --> 00:37:46,498
-OH, NO, I DON'T LIKE THIS.
WELL, IT'S -- IT'S STUPID.

649
00:37:46,532 --> 00:37:48,434
SHE CAN'T EVEN USE IT.
IT'S GOT THE WRONG PICTURE.

650
00:37:48,467 --> 00:37:50,802
-YEAH, BUT IF IT WAS A REAL
PICTURE, WE'D KNOW WHO SHE IS.

651
00:37:50,836 --> 00:37:53,071
-IT'S JUST -- I DON'T GET WHY
SOMEONE WOULD WANT AN I.D.

652
00:37:53,104 --> 00:37:55,273
THAT THEY CAN'T EVEN USE.

653
00:37:55,307 --> 00:37:57,576
-WHO THE HELL YOU THINK
KELLY HANSON IS?

654
00:37:57,609 --> 00:38:00,746
-ARE YOU JUST GONNA STAND THERE
OR SAY SOMETHING USEFUL?

655
00:38:00,779 --> 00:38:02,881
-SHE TEXTED ME.

656
00:38:02,914 --> 00:38:04,683
-WELL, WHAT'D IT SAY?

657
00:38:04,716 --> 00:38:07,853
-SHE SENT ME
A SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER.

658
00:38:07,886 --> 00:38:09,054
-FOR WHAT?

659
00:38:09,087 --> 00:38:11,723
-I DON'T KNOW.

660
00:38:11,757 --> 00:38:13,892
-I THINK, UM --

661
00:38:13,925 --> 00:38:15,193
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

662
00:38:15,226 --> 00:38:17,396
SHE MIGHT WANT US TO USE IT
WITH THIS.

663
00:38:20,366 --> 00:38:23,268
[ SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE ]

664
00:38:25,704 --> 00:38:29,641
-RICKY WAS THE NEXT ONE
TO GET A CALL.

665
00:38:30,776 --> 00:38:33,144
[ PHONE VIBRATING ]

666
00:38:43,889 --> 00:38:45,424
-YES?

667
00:38:45,457 --> 00:38:47,058
-a copy of your parents' rental

668
00:38:47,092 --> 00:38:49,928
would sure go nicely with
your friends' new information.

669
00:38:49,961 --> 00:38:52,230
[ CLICK ]

670
00:39:00,105 --> 00:39:03,542
-WE KNEW BRITTANY WAS HAVING US
GATHER PIECES TO A PUZZLE.

671
00:39:03,575 --> 00:39:07,846
WE JUST HAD NO IDEA WHAT THE
PUZZLE WAS GOING TO ADD UP TO.

672
00:39:07,879 --> 00:39:11,717
AND WE SHOULD HAVE REALIZED
THAT WITH SOCIAL SECURITY
NUMBERS AND LEASES,

673
00:39:11,750 --> 00:39:14,820
WE WERE GETTING INTO SOMETHING
A LOT MORE SERIOUS

674
00:39:14,853 --> 00:39:17,423
THAN JUST CHANGING GRADES.

675
00:39:39,310 --> 00:39:41,312
-[ SNORING ]

676
00:39:53,358 --> 00:39:57,663
-SO, WE HAVE AN I.D., A SOCIAL
SECURITY NUMBER, AND A LEASE.

677
00:40:00,165 --> 00:40:02,100
-WE'RE MAKING
AN IMAGINARY PERSON.

678
00:40:02,133 --> 00:40:04,369
-YEAH, THAT'S WHAT A FAKE I.D.
IS FOR, GENIUS.

679
00:40:04,402 --> 00:40:08,807
-NO, THIS IS MORE THAN THAT.
WE'RE CREATING A PERSON THAT
EXISTS LEGALLY ON PAPER.

680
00:40:08,840 --> 00:40:10,609
-WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

681
00:40:10,642 --> 00:40:13,011
-IT MEANS GO TO JAIL, RICKY,
GO DIRECTLY TO JAIL.

682
00:40:13,044 --> 00:40:15,814
DON'T GRADUATE HIGH SCHOOL,
DON'T COLLECT ANY GRADUATION
MONEY.

683
00:40:15,847 --> 00:40:18,383
[ PHONE VIBRATES ]

684
00:40:18,416 --> 00:40:20,251
-WHAT IS IT?

685
00:40:20,285 --> 00:40:21,853
ALEX!

686
00:40:21,887 --> 00:40:23,421
-ACCOUNT WNB.

687
00:40:23,455 --> 00:40:25,323
-WHAT?
-WHAT?

688
00:40:26,357 --> 00:40:27,926
-WELD NATIONAL.

689
00:40:27,959 --> 00:40:31,730
GUYS, S-SHE WANTS US
TO SET UP A BANK ACCOUNT.

690
00:40:46,645 --> 00:40:49,781
[ COMPUTER CLACKING ]

691
00:40:56,154 --> 00:41:00,659
-YOU CAN GET THE MAIL
BEFORE YOUR PARENTS, RIGHT?

692
00:41:00,692 --> 00:41:02,093
-YES.

693
00:41:02,127 --> 00:41:04,496
THEY WORK LATE.

694
00:41:04,530 --> 00:41:07,298
-I HOPE THIS WORKS.

695
00:41:19,244 --> 00:41:22,080
-I COULDN'T BELIEVE
HOW EASY IT WAS.

696
00:41:22,113 --> 00:41:26,484
A PHOTO I.D., A SOCIAL SECURITY
NUMBER, AND PROOF OF RESIDENCE

697
00:41:26,518 --> 00:41:29,220
WAS ALL WE NEEDED
TO OPEN A BANK ACCOUNT.

698
00:41:29,988 --> 00:41:32,257
WITH A FEW PIECES
OF INFORMATION,

699
00:41:32,290 --> 00:41:34,492
WE MADE A PERSON
OUT OF THIN AIR,

700
00:41:34,526 --> 00:41:36,628
AND ALL I KEPT
THINKING ABOUT WAS,

701
00:41:36,662 --> 00:41:38,964
WHO COULD BE DOING THIS TO US?

702
00:41:38,997 --> 00:41:42,634
AND MORE IMPORTANTLY,
WHEN WOULD IT STOP?

703
00:41:42,668 --> 00:41:43,902
-ALEX.

704
00:41:43,935 --> 00:41:46,171
COME HERE.

705
00:41:46,204 --> 00:41:47,472
YOU OKAY?

706
00:41:47,505 --> 00:41:49,875
-NOT REALLY.

707
00:41:49,908 --> 00:41:51,943
-ALL RIGHT, LOOK.
I'VE BEEN DOING SOME THINKING.

708
00:41:51,977 --> 00:41:53,945
EVEN IF WE COULD TRACK
THE CELLPHONE NUMBER,

709
00:41:53,979 --> 00:41:56,615
IT'S PROBABLY JUST A BURNER,
ANYWAYS, SO --
-WHAT?

710
00:41:56,648 --> 00:42:00,385
-IT'S A PREPAID PHONE
WITH NO PLAN, SO NO RECORDS.

711
00:42:00,418 --> 00:42:02,387
WELL, I DID FIND THIS.

712
00:42:02,420 --> 00:42:04,322
-WHAT IS IT?

713
00:42:04,355 --> 00:42:07,492
-I SAW THIS THING ON THE NEWS
ABOUT HOW THEY TRACK
INTERNET PERVERTS

714
00:42:07,525 --> 00:42:09,561
BY TRACING THEIR I.P. ADDRESS,
AND BAS--

715
00:42:09,595 --> 00:42:12,097
-WHAT'S AN I.P. ADDRESS?

716
00:42:12,130 --> 00:42:15,233
-IT'S LIKE
AN INTERNET FINGERPRINT
THAT ALL COMPUTERS HAVE.

717
00:42:15,266 --> 00:42:17,636
ANYWAYS, I LOG INTO THE ACCOUNT
BRITTANY GAVE YOU,

718
00:42:17,669 --> 00:42:19,404
AND I SPENT ALL MORNING
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT

719
00:42:19,437 --> 00:42:20,939
HOW TO TRACE
THE E-MAIL SHE SENT.

720
00:42:20,972 --> 00:42:22,574
THIS IS WHAT I FOUND.

721
00:42:22,608 --> 00:42:25,143
THE SIGNAL WAS COMING FROM HERE.

722
00:42:25,176 --> 00:42:26,978
IT'S ARCHER.

723
00:42:27,012 --> 00:42:29,715
WHOEVER WAS TALKING TO US
THE OTHER NIGHT WAS DOING IT
FROM THE SCHOOL.

724
00:42:29,748 --> 00:42:32,150
AND I DON'T KNOW HOW YET,

725
00:42:32,183 --> 00:42:34,319
BUT WE'RE ONE STEP CLOSER

726
00:42:34,352 --> 00:42:36,387
TO NAILING THIS ASSHOLE.

727
00:42:37,488 --> 00:42:38,957
-[ SCOFFS ]

728
00:42:38,990 --> 00:42:42,761
WELL, LET'S JUST FOLLOW
BRITTANY'S EXAMPLE.

729
00:42:46,131 --> 00:42:49,034
-IF BRITTANY VIDEO CHATTED US
FROM ARCHER,

730
00:42:49,067 --> 00:42:51,402
THEN ALL WE'D HAVE TO DO WAS
FIND THE SURVEILLANCE FOOTAGE

731
00:42:51,436 --> 00:42:53,238
FROM THAT NIGHT.

732
00:42:53,271 --> 00:42:56,107
SHE PROBABLY THOUGHT WE WERE
JUST SITTING AROUND
BEING SCARED,

733
00:42:56,141 --> 00:42:58,944
JUST WAITING TO BE TOLD
WHAT TO DO NEXT.

734
00:42:58,977 --> 00:43:04,015
BUT IF WE FOUND THAT FOOTAGE, WE
WOULD KNOW EXACTLY WHO SHE WAS.

735
00:43:07,719 --> 00:43:09,721
-WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

736
00:43:09,755 --> 00:43:11,657
-[ Russian accent ]
MY APOLOGIES.

737
00:43:11,690 --> 00:43:14,325
I THOUGHT THE ICE CREAM
REMIND YOU OF THE GULAG.

738
00:43:14,359 --> 00:43:17,663
-[ SPEAKING RUSSIAN ]

739
00:43:25,403 --> 00:43:27,438
SON OF A BITCH!
HUH?!

740
00:43:27,472 --> 00:43:30,275
-[ Normal voice ] YOU SHOULDN'T
TALK ABOUT YOUR MOTHER
THAT WAY, RICKY.

741
00:43:30,308 --> 00:43:32,844
-WELL, AT LEAST
MY MOTHER NEVER SLEPT
WITH MY LITTLE LEAGUE COACH.

742
00:43:32,878 --> 00:43:34,713
-I TOLD YOU THAT SHIT
IN CONFIDENCE.

743
00:43:34,746 --> 00:43:36,948
-HUH? WELL, WHAT YOU
GONNA DO ABOUT IT?! HUH?

744
00:43:36,982 --> 00:43:38,283
COME ON!

745
00:43:38,316 --> 00:43:39,685
-[ SNIFFS ]

746
00:43:39,718 --> 00:43:42,520
YOU SMELL THAT?
[ SNIFFS ]

747
00:43:42,553 --> 00:43:44,522
I SMELL THIS VAGINA.
IT SMELLS LIKE COMMUNISM.

748
00:43:44,555 --> 00:43:47,158
-OOH!
-OOH!

749
00:43:47,192 --> 00:43:49,928
-WELL, YOU BETTER WATCH OUT
FOR MR. RANDALS.

750
00:43:49,961 --> 00:43:51,196
COME ON!

751
00:43:51,229 --> 00:43:54,165
[ ALL SHOUTING ]

752
00:43:54,199 --> 00:43:56,334
-YOUR MOTHER'S VAGINA
SMELLS LIKE SALT...

753
00:43:56,367 --> 00:43:57,568
-OH, YOU!
-HUH?

754
00:43:57,602 --> 00:44:00,939
NYET, NYET, NYET, NYET!

755
00:44:00,972 --> 00:44:03,108
HOW YOU LIKE THAT, RUSSIAN BOY?
YOU LIKE THAT?

756
00:44:03,141 --> 00:44:04,642
-KGB THIS!

757
00:44:04,676 --> 00:44:08,646
-OFFICER RANDALS, WE NEED YOU
IN THE CAFETERIA.

758
00:44:12,117 --> 00:44:13,484
-RIGHT AWAY?

759
00:44:13,518 --> 00:44:16,521
-Yes, right away.
We have a fight.

760
00:44:39,010 --> 00:44:41,880
-WHAT THE --
NONE OF THESE SCREENS
ARE WORKING.

761
00:44:41,913 --> 00:44:43,314
THEY'RE NOT TURNING ON.

762
00:44:43,348 --> 00:44:45,216
-START PRESSING THINGS.

763
00:44:45,250 --> 00:44:47,518
-[ SCOFFS, SIGHS ]

764
00:44:47,552 --> 00:44:49,654
-HEY! HEY!
MAKE A PATH, MAKE A PATH!

765
00:44:49,687 --> 00:44:50,989
YOU TWO, BREAK IT UP!

766
00:44:51,022 --> 00:44:53,859
STOP IT, STOP IT!
BREAK IT UP!

767
00:44:53,892 --> 00:44:55,827
EVERYBODY GO BACK TO EATING
THEIR LUNCHES!

768
00:44:55,861 --> 00:44:57,662
CALM DOWN!
YOU'RE COMING WITH ME!

769
00:44:57,695 --> 00:45:00,098
LET'S GO, CAMERON!
COME ON!

770
00:45:02,667 --> 00:45:05,937
-OKAY, I THINK
I FOUND SOMETHING.

771
00:45:07,172 --> 00:45:09,640
-SPEAK ENGLISH, ALL RIGHT?
-OKAY.

772
00:45:09,674 --> 00:45:11,509
-W-WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?
-WHAT'S WRONG?

773
00:45:11,542 --> 00:45:14,079
-THERE'S LIKE -- THERE'S LIKE
A MILLION FOLDERS IN HERE.

774
00:45:14,112 --> 00:45:16,481
-JUST TAKE WHATEVER YOU CAN.
-ARE YOU STUPID?!

775
00:45:16,514 --> 00:45:18,349
THAT'S NOT HOW THIS WORKS!
-SHH!

776
00:45:18,383 --> 00:45:21,019
-COME ON, YOU TWO.
SIT!

777
00:45:21,052 --> 00:45:23,021
-THERE'S TOO MANY FILES IN HERE,
AND THEY'RE WAY TOO BIG.

778
00:45:23,054 --> 00:45:25,090
-CAN'T YOU JUST E-MAIL THEM
TO YOUR HOUSE?

779
00:45:25,123 --> 00:45:27,993
-JUST SHUT UP, OKAY?
I'M TRYING TO THINK,
AND YOU'RE NOT HELPING!

780
00:45:29,394 --> 00:45:32,831
-KEEP YOUR HANDS TO YOURSELVES.
THE PRINCIPAL WILL BE WITH YOU
IN A MINUTE.

781
00:45:32,864 --> 00:45:35,700
AND WATCH YOUR MOUTH.

782
00:45:48,313 --> 00:45:49,614
-ANYTHING?

783
00:45:49,647 --> 00:45:53,151
-I DON'T KNOW WHICH CAMERA
IS WHICH.

784
00:45:53,184 --> 00:45:55,720
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
KEEPING WATCH.

785
00:45:58,289 --> 00:45:59,590
-He's back.

786
00:45:59,624 --> 00:46:02,260
He's back, Jack.

787
00:46:02,293 --> 00:46:04,695
-SHIT.

788
00:46:05,596 --> 00:46:07,732
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

789
00:46:07,765 --> 00:46:11,702
-UH, I THINK
I SAW SOME KIDS SMOKING POT
IN THE UPSTAIRS BATHROOM.

790
00:46:11,736 --> 00:46:13,771
I JUST THOUGHT YOU SHOULD KNOW.

791
00:46:13,805 --> 00:46:17,175
-LET'S GO. LET'S GO.

792
00:46:21,012 --> 00:46:22,247
[ SIGHS ]

793
00:46:32,157 --> 00:46:35,827
-OH, MY GOD.

794
00:46:35,861 --> 00:46:38,396
[ BIRD CHIRPING ]

795
00:46:38,429 --> 00:46:41,566
-SO, YOU MEAN WE GOT THREE MORE
DAYS OF I.S.S. FOR NO REASON?
-LIKE YOU CARE.

796
00:46:41,599 --> 00:46:44,602
-A BIG PART OF ME WANTS
YOUR BRAINS AT THE BOTTOM
OF MY SHOES RIGHT NOW.

797
00:46:44,635 --> 00:46:46,104
-LOOK,
IT'S A COMPLICATED SYSTEM.

798
00:46:46,137 --> 00:46:47,705
IT WOULD HAVE TAKEN US
ALL DAY TO FIGURE OUT.

799
00:46:47,738 --> 00:46:49,174
-HOW COMPLICATED COULD IT BE?
-YOU KNOW WHAT?!

800
00:46:49,207 --> 00:46:51,276
IF IT WAS UP TO ME, YOU WOULDN'T
BE IN CHARGE, OKAY?!

801
00:46:51,309 --> 00:46:53,578
-RICKY, THIS IS WHY I SAID
LET US HANDLE IT INSTEAD
OF THESE TWO LOSERS.

802
00:46:53,611 --> 00:46:55,246
-WAIT, GUYS, STOP.

803
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:58,083
WHO WOULD HAVE THE TIME TO SIT
IN THE SECURITY OFFICE FOR HOURS

804
00:46:58,116 --> 00:47:00,651
AND FIGURE OUT
THE SURVEILLANCE SYSTEM?

805
00:47:01,486 --> 00:47:03,354
-THEY'D NEED A SET OF KEYS.

806
00:47:03,388 --> 00:47:05,991
-EXACTLY, SO THEN IT CAN'T BE
A STUDENT.

807
00:47:06,024 --> 00:47:08,359
GUYS, WHOEVER MADE THIS PROFILE

808
00:47:08,393 --> 00:47:11,963
WOULD HAVE TO HAVE ACCESS
TO THE SCHOOL WHENEVER
THEY WANTED TO.

809
00:47:13,531 --> 00:47:15,733
BRITTANY MUST WORK AT ARCHER.

810
00:47:15,766 --> 00:47:19,737
-AND WHO KNOWS
THE SECURITY SYSTEM BETTER
THAN OFFICER RANDALS?

811
00:47:21,772 --> 00:47:25,510
WE SPLIT OUR TIME UP
THE BEST THAT WE COULD.

812
00:47:25,543 --> 00:47:27,345
WHENEVER SOMEONE
HAD A FREE PERIOD

813
00:47:27,378 --> 00:47:30,115
OR COULD GET AWAY FROM CLASS,
SPORTS, ANYTHING,

814
00:47:30,148 --> 00:47:33,551
THEN THEY WOULD FOLLOW
OFFICER RANDALS.

815
00:47:33,584 --> 00:47:37,622
IF WE CAUGHT HIM
SENDING ONE OF US A TEXT OR
DOING ANYTHING INCRIMINATING,

816
00:47:37,655 --> 00:47:39,991
THEN WE WOULD JUMP ON HIM.

817
00:47:40,025 --> 00:47:41,927
IT MADE PERFECT SENSE.

818
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:43,828
HE HAD A DEAD-END JOB

819
00:47:43,861 --> 00:47:46,264
WITH PROBABLY
AN EQUALLY DEPRESSING SALARY.

820
00:47:46,297 --> 00:47:50,501
NOBODY GROWS UP ASPIRING TO BE
A SECURITY GUARD.

821
00:47:50,535 --> 00:47:52,203
PEOPLE WAIT THEIR ENTIRE LIVES

822
00:47:52,237 --> 00:47:56,374
TO POUNCE ON AN OPPORTUNITY
THAT CAN CHANGE THEIR SITUATION.

823
00:47:58,609 --> 00:48:00,878
[ PHONE BEEPS ]

824
00:48:07,818 --> 00:48:10,855
-[ CHUCKLES ]
DAMN.

825
00:48:30,375 --> 00:48:32,143
-[ KNOCKS ON WINDOW ]

826
00:48:40,351 --> 00:48:42,420
-[ CHUCKLES ]

827
00:48:50,428 --> 00:48:52,964
-LET'S GO.

828
00:49:07,378 --> 00:49:09,747
[ KEYS JANGLE ]

829
00:49:12,450 --> 00:49:16,154
-LOOK, I'M AT RANDALS' HOUSE,
SO...I DON'T KNOW.

830
00:49:16,187 --> 00:49:18,923
GIVE ME A CALL
WHEN YOU GET THIS.

831
00:49:18,956 --> 00:49:20,825
[ WIND HOWLING ]

832
00:49:29,467 --> 00:49:31,202
[ PHONE VIBRATES ]

833
00:49:38,276 --> 00:49:39,777
HELLO?

834
00:49:40,645 --> 00:49:45,250
-It's finally your time
to shine, Mr. President.

835
00:49:48,486 --> 00:49:50,921
[ CROWD CHEERING ]

836
00:49:57,328 --> 00:49:59,564
-I CAN'T BELIEVE WE'RE AT
A GODDAMN FOOTBALL GAME.

837
00:49:59,597 --> 00:50:02,500
-I CAN'T BELIEVE WE THOUGHT
THAT UGLY BASTARD RANDALS

838
00:50:02,533 --> 00:50:04,035
WAS BEHIND BRITTANY TAMMAND.

839
00:50:04,069 --> 00:50:06,037
-AT THIS POINT,
IT COULD BE ANYONE.

840
00:50:06,071 --> 00:50:09,507
[ RADIO STATIC ]
-Miss Sedgewick.

841
00:50:09,540 --> 00:50:13,144
Miss Sedgewick, come in.

842
00:50:13,178 --> 00:50:14,779
Miss Sedgewick, come down
to my office, pl--

843
00:50:14,812 --> 00:50:16,714
[ CLICK ]

844
00:50:16,747 --> 00:50:18,249
-GO AHEAD.

845
00:50:18,283 --> 00:50:21,586
-AT EVERY EVENT, THE
BOOSTER CLUB SELLS CONCESSIONS.

846
00:50:21,619 --> 00:50:23,921
T-SHIRTS AND SWEATSHIRTS

847
00:50:23,954 --> 00:50:26,824
AND JUST STUPID TRINKETS
FOR PARENTS.

848
00:50:26,857 --> 00:50:29,927
SO BEFORE EVERY GAME,
PRINCIPAL DONATO

849
00:50:29,960 --> 00:50:31,396
WITHDRAWS ENOUGH MONEY
FOR CHANGE

850
00:50:31,429 --> 00:50:34,732
AND THEN DEPOSITS THE TAKE
THE NEXT MORNING.

851
00:50:34,765 --> 00:50:36,601
-WERE YOU GONNA STEAL THE CASH?

852
00:50:39,437 --> 00:50:42,006
-NOT EXACTLY.

853
00:50:43,941 --> 00:50:45,843
JACK WAS IN CHARGE
OF THE BOOSTER CLUB

854
00:50:45,876 --> 00:50:47,545
HIS FIRST TWO YEARS AT ARCHER.

855
00:50:47,578 --> 00:50:49,780
HE KNEW DONATO
KEPT THE DEPOSIT SLIPS

856
00:50:49,814 --> 00:50:52,283
IN THE CASH DRAWER
AT EVERY GAME.

857
00:50:53,584 --> 00:50:55,086
WE WEREN'T GONNA STEAL THE CASH.

858
00:50:55,120 --> 00:50:58,156
WHAT BRITTANY WANTED
WAS THE ACCOUNT NUMBER.

859
00:50:58,856 --> 00:51:00,691
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

860
00:51:00,725 --> 00:51:02,493
-I, UH -- I --

861
00:51:02,527 --> 00:51:05,996
-YOU SHOULD BE OUT THERE LEADING
THE CHEER, MR. CLASS PRESIDENT.

862
00:51:06,030 --> 00:51:09,767
GO ON, GET OUT THERE.
-YES, SIR.

863
00:51:09,800 --> 00:51:11,236
[ CROWD CHEERING ]
-YEAH!

864
00:51:11,269 --> 00:51:13,838
[ LAUGHS ]
STAMPEDE!

865
00:51:13,871 --> 00:51:15,173
[ CHUCKLES ]

866
00:51:18,876 --> 00:51:20,478
-AFTER WE GOT
THE ACCOUNT NUMBER,

867
00:51:20,511 --> 00:51:22,313
